한글 설명서    ｜    中文简介与讨论 What is Officiser?Officiser is a unique, fun and effective sedentary lifestyle solution for anyone who sit 4+ hours a day. It is an innovative gadget that incorporated the health and productivity benefits of an under-desk exerciser and an ergonomic footrest. And it is also the world's first fitness device that implemented ankle rolling function (patent-pending) which most naturally mimics the walking motion. Officiser is fun and easy to use, and the movements feel as natural as fidgeting. And you can use it at home and in the office, and anywhere you want to.Officiser is co-designed by SAIDII, Red Dot Design Award Winner, CTL(Changing The Lifestyle) Ltd. and Ryan Cho, Ergonomic Expert. And It Is Vetted By Danahan Clinic.   Product Concept and EngineeringOfficiser is designed to be used throughout the day whenever you sit to increase physical activity (Some call it NEAT/NEPA, Non-exercise Activity Thermogenesis/Non-exercise Physical Activity ) and reduce the potential physical inactivity time. That is distinctly different from typical exercisers which you use during the short workout sessions. To realise those requirements, Officiser is full of unique technical innovations, including the world’s first zero-gravity glide system and ankle-rolling function. And you will be amazed by how much more physical activity you can gain from using Officiser during the 8 hour work time - the effect is similar to walking 15 to 25 miles a day! And the extra calorie burn is similar to 60+ minutes of intensive gym workout! Why "zero-gravity" glide? We believe the device that can be used all day have to be intuitive and fun to use. And it also needs to give you a stable upper body so that your normal work productivity won’t be affected by using Officiser. We are inspired by the leg swaying and foot pedaling kids naturally do while they sit by the pool. And we have tested hundreds of rail systems and tension combinations to find the motion that we wanted. Officiser's easy glide feels exactly like pedalling in water or as some testers said, walking on the cloud. It is an enjoyable movement that you don’t want to stop.Why ankle-rolling? The ankle rolling feature not only has its unique physical benefits like stimulating diverse muscle groups and increase joints flexibility, but it also substantially intensified the gliding movements without affecting your upper body posture. Our muscles strain easily from small and repetitive actions. But with ankle-rolling and zero-gravity glide, Officiser offers dynamic movements at a larger range that not only avoid the muscle strains and fatigue, but effectively stretches and strengthens the muscles.  Why Do You Need An Officiser?Officiser is created to address the problem of insufficient physical activity as a result of prolonged sitting, which is detrimental to our health, regardless of regular exercise ( i.e. moderate to intensive workout for  30-60 minutes a day). In fact, the World Health Organization (WHO) has identified physical inactivity as an independent risk factor for chronic disease development, and it is now the fourth leading cause of death worldwide. (Watch a TED-ed video on the negative effects of sitting)Physical activity reduces body fat and blood pressure, increases muscle strength and endurance and improves flexibility and posture. And it is not only good for your body, but also helps your brain to stay sharp and energized, it has been scientifically proven to increase focus and memory, improve creativity and decision making, reduce stress and anxiety, and prevent cognitive decline. Officiser can help you to stay active while you sit at your desk or sofa, which will:
Boost your calorie burn;
Improve focus and energy levels;
Develop good posture - less strains on neck/back;
Strengthen diverse muscle groups and joints;
Improve blood circulation;
Lessen leg swelling ;
Reduce muscle cramps/numbness;
Prevent cardiovascular diseases, type II diabetes, and organ damage by reducing time of physical inactivity.
More details in the Features & Benefits section below.If you are a fidgeter, Officiser will provide you an elegant way to 'fidget' at the office and in the classroom. We made Officiser because we found the existing sedentary lifestyle (prolonged sitting) solutions in the market cannot satisfy our needs. Listed below is the comparison between Officiser and some popular workplace solutions (Click here if you cannot see the image clearly).  REWARD OPTIONSAll price listed below is in US Dollars. 1. Officiser helps you to keep a good posture. Officiser helps you to naturally develop better posture while you sit. (Watch a video)  It will prevent you from unhealthy habits like crossing your legs, hunching your back, leaning on one side. And you will unconsciously get into the habit of sitting in the right posture.  2. Officiser boosts your calorie burn by increasing your NEAT (Non-exercise Activity Thermogenesis). (What is NEAT?)As its name suggest, NEAT is the energy you burn through physical activities other than sport like exercises. And it can account for as little as 15% of energy expenditure in the very sedentary and up to 50% in very active individuals. And it is a critical factor in human obesity and overall health. Our test has shown that Officiser can significantly boost your NEAT while you sit. In the test, we tracked two office workers for two weeks during the 8-hour work hours (One week not using Officiser, the other week using Officiser), monitoring their heart rates, oxygen saturation, VCO2, and respiration rate. And we calculated the calorie burn based on the results. The graph above shows us the comparison of the average calorie burn in an hour without or with officising. We can see significant increase in calories burnt per hour when officising compared to just sitting. For those two workers we tested, the extra calorie burn per 8 hour work day is equivalent to an hour of intense exercise in the gym (or 1+ hour of jogging). Or, to put it into context, using Officiser is similar to walking 3-5 miles per hour depending on your movement types.  3. Officiser can help you to increase blood circulation, increase focus & energy,  and reduce stress. (We used thermocam to track the temperature in different part of the body. The more the dot aligned, the better: it means the body temperature is more evenly distributed and the blood circulation is better.)Blood circulation is an essential to your health. Better blood circulation means more oxygen and energy to different part of your body, including brain, organs, and extremities. It improves brain performance which helps keep your mind sharp and focused. And it also leads to healthier skin and lower blood pressure. In addition, better blood circulation reduces/prevents numbness in your legs and feet. Learn more about our test and the benefits of good blood circulation, check out this video we made.  4. Officiser can help you stretch, stimulate and relax your muscles.You can use Officiser to make dynamic moves, which can stimulate muscles on your abs, glutes, legs and lower back. A. Gliding Push/Pull Effect: improves knee stability and flexibility. B. Ankle Stretches and Heel PullEffect: strengthen muscles around ankles, increase flexibility of anklesUsing Officiser is as natural as fidgeting. You can go with the flow while you sit and make your own combination of movements. Furthermore, you can also use Officiser to create exercise routine for yourself  (One of our stretch goal is to create a guidebook with exercise recommendation). One exercise move we love is the body rotation, which trains your core muscle and is great for your spine and it relaxes your tight back. One more thing, Officiser can be used with shoes or without shoes. Even office ladies with high heels can also use Officiser easily and comfortably. And we provided optional acupressure sole for more stimulation and relaxation for using Officiser without shoes. 5. Officiser will help you to reverse leg swellingLack of circulation is one of the common reason for lower body swelling. And many people experience leg swelling after sitting or standing for a long periods of time. As Officiser increases circulation, we expect officising will reduce leg swelling. And our test confirmed this belief. In the test, we measured the circumference of left and right calves of an office lady in the morning (9:00am) and noon (1:00pm), and then we gave her the Officiser to use. We can see from the graph above that the circumference is almost back to the morning status after a mere 45 minute of officising. RecognitionOfficiser team was selected among thousands to participate theMIT Global Entrepreneurial BootcampOfficiser is currently in WESC, one of the most selective incubators in South Korea As seen on:The Officiser team is based in Seoul, South Korea with team members/partners in Melbourne, Australia and Beijing, China. Media Contact: Jie Min Email: jie@officiser.com  ----------------References: papers and articles that we collected.
